<L>__{interior whale's house bedroom day}
<A>__{whale and hanna go through the closet together.}
<C>__{hanna}
<D>__{mr. boone. he is an interesting friend.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{i'd hardly call our yardman a friend.}
<C>__{hanna}
<D>__{no. but someone you can talk to.}
<A>__{whale stops, turns to hanna.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{do you miss having someone to talk to, hanna?}
<C>__{hanna}
<D>__{i have my family. also our lord jesus christ.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{of course. how is the old boy these days?}
<A>__{the naughty remark is met with a solemn stare. whale reaches up, chooses a lightweight blue suit.}
<C>__{whale}
<D>__{it needs a hat. there was a wide brimmed cream fedora...}
<C>__{hanna}
<D>__{it must be up in your old room. i will look.}
<A>__{the phone rings. hanna hurries to answer it.}
